{
  "schema_version": "1.0",
  "name": "NE555 Astable Multivibrator",
  "description": "Free-running oscillator. Output is a square wave. Frequency and duty cycle set by R1, R2, C1. Pin 4 (RST) tied high. Pin 5 (CV) bypassed to ground via C2.",
  "notes": "f = 1.44 / ((R1 + 2×R2) × C1). Duty cycle = (R1+R2)/(R1+2×R2). With R1=1kΩ, R2=10kΩ, C1=10µF: f ≈ 6.7Hz. LED blinks visible. C2=10nF on pin 5 recommended to reduce noise.",
  "components": [
    {"id":1,"type":"ne555","ref":"U1","x":0,"y":0,"rotation":0,"flipH":false,"value":"NE555","notes":""},
    {"id":2,"type":"resistor","ref":"R1","x":-100,"y":-80,"rotation":0,"flipH":false,"value":"1kΩ","notes":"Timing resistor — part of charge path"},
    {"id":3,"type":"resistor","ref":"R2","x":-100,"y":-40,"rotation":0,"flipH":false,"value":"10kΩ","notes":"Timing resistor — part of charge/discharge path"},
    {"id":4,"type":"cap_elec","ref":"C1","x":-100,"y":60,"rotation":90,"flipH":false,"value":"10µF","notes":"Timing capacitor — charged via R1+R2, discharged via R2"},
